  "prompt": "Adoption: How can I find my biological parents in China?",
  "response": "Finding biological parents in China can be challenging, but here are some potential steps:\n\n1. Official Channels:\n- Contact the orphanage where you were adopted\n- Check with the provincial adoption authorities\n- Seek help from the China Center of Adoption Affairs\n\n2. Documentation Research:\n- Review your adoption documents\n- Look for original birth records or finding location details\n- Gather any information about your birth province/city\n\n3. DNA Testing Options:\n- Use DNA databases like 23andMe\n- Join Chinese adoptee DNA matching groups\n- Consider specialized adoption DNA services\n\n4. Online Resources:\n- Join adoption search forums\n- Connect with Chinese adoptee support groups\n- Use social media platforms for searching\n\n5. Professional Help:\n- Hire a professional searcher in China\n- Work with adoption search agencies specializing in Chinese adoptions\n- Consult with organizations like \"Find My Family\"\n\n6. Legal Considerations:\n- Understand China's privacy laws\n- Be prepared for potential emotional challenges\n- Consider potential cultural and language barriers\n\n7. Emotional Preparation:\n- Seek counseling or support groups\n- Have realistic expectations\n- Prepare for potential outcomes\n\nEach search is unique, and success depends on individual circumstances.",
